{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_2","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' task-plans/no-editor-first-workflows-task-plan.md\"","aggregated_output":"# No Editor First Workflows Task Plan\n\n## Priority\n\nPriority 2\n\n## Objective\n\nMake the managed center the default place for routine agent operations.\n\n## Scope\n\n- send prompt from cards\n- loop control from cards\n- inspect without opening extra surfaces\n- log/result visibility inside cards and drawer\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Task 1 — Card-Level Operations\n\n- [x] keep prompt send, Codex jump, and loop actions usable from board cards\n- [x] reduce unnecessary editor or terminal jumps\n\n### Task 2 — Embedded Status and Logs\n\n- [x] show enough runtime/log context inside cards and drawer\n- [x] avoid forcing users to open log files for common checks\n\n### Task 3 — Controlled Fallbacks\n\n- [ ] use editor/terminal only when needed\n- [ ] make fallback actions explicit rather than surprising\n\n## Constraints\n\nThis is a design target, not an absolute rule. Some actions will still need external surfaces.\n\n## Exit Criteria\n\n- common workflows stay inside the managed center\n- editor and terminal become fallback tools, not the default control path\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
